<paragraph id="8BED36DB04775210FF03D48CFDBDFB7C" blockId="1.[174,1233,1109,1520]" pageId="1" pageNumber="76">
B i o l o g y. Develops in old wood of dead but staying willows and poplars (Lukjanovich, Arnoldi, 1951; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC34B2A04775210FEBED4ECFDAAFB7C" author="Folwaczny, B." box="[350,549,1237,1264]" pageId="1" pageNumber="76" pagination="65 - 180" refId="ref2333" refString="Folwaczny, B. 1973. Bestimmungstabelle der palaarktischen Cossoninae (Coleoptera, Curculionidae) - ohne die nur in China und Japan vorkommenden Gattungen, nebst Angaben zur Verbreitung. Entomologische Blatter, 69 (2), 65 - 180." type="journal article" year="1973">Folwaczny, 1973</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BED36DB04775210FF03D4CCFD31FA7C" blockId="1.[174,1233,1109,1520]" pageId="1" pageNumber="76">
D i a g n o s i s. This species can be recognized from externally similar 
<taxonomicName id="4C524D5804775210FBCAD4CFFF55FABC" pageId="1" pageNumber="76">
<emphasis id="B926EAC904775210FBCAD4CFFB1AFA9C" box="[1066,1173,1270,1296]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="76">Cossonus</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C524D5804775210FF0DD52FFC9FFABC" authority="Sahlberg, 1835" authorityName="Sahlberg" authorityYear="1835" box="[237,784,1301,1328]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Cossonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cylindricus" subGenus="Caenocossonus">
<emphasis id="B926EAC904775210FF0DD52FFE8FFABC" box="[237,256,1302,1328]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="76">C</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis id="B926EAC904775210FEF9D52FFE48FABC" box="[281,455,1302,1328]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="76">Caenocossonus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B926EAC904775210FE3AD52CFDD8FAA3" box="[474,599,1301,1327]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="76">cylindricus</emphasis>
Sahlberg, 1835
</taxonomicName>
) with rostrum not widened in Ơ and dilated basally in 
<specimenCount id="9D54FD5204775210FE60D50DFE1CFADD" box="[384,403,1332,1361]" pageId="1" pageNumber="76" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
. From wider distributed 
<taxonomicName id="4C524D5804775210FD22D50FFC0FFAC3" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1838" box="[706,896,1333,1359]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Mesites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallidipennis">
<emphasis id="B926EAC904775210FD22D50FFC0FFAC3" box="[706,896,1333,1359]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="76">M. pallidipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it differs by nearly unicolor body, evident microsculpture on pronotum, elytral interstriae narrower then striae, sparse interstrial punctures weakly enlargered on declivity; slightly widened from the base to its middle median lobe of aedeagus with apical portion almost parallelsided and apical edge wide rounded; wide divergent at the base and inner subparallel arms of sternite VIII in female; feeding in dead wood, not driftwood.
</paragraph>
